I wrote a subclass of the middleware class LogSetupMiddleWare to use a different filter.  It didnt work because you have a hardcoded RequestFilter instead of the self.FILTER in the process_request function.

This works.

{code}
def process_request(self, request):
    """Adds a filter, bound to *request*, to the appropriate loggers."""
    request.logging_filter = self.FILTER(request)
    self.add_filter(request.logging_filter)
{code}

